<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">&nbsp;</spa=
n><o:p></o:p></p>
<div>
<div style=3D"border:none;border-top:solid #E1E1E1 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in =
0in 0in">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">From:</span></b><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;=
font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"> Grant Metson &lt;<a href=3D"ma=
ilto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;
<br>
<b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, 14 October 2025 4:51 PM<br>
<b>To:</b> Raffaella del Prete &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:raffaellanz@icloud.com=
">raffaellanz@icloud.com</a>&gt;<br>
<b>Cc:</b> Abigail Collin &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Abigail.Collin@wynnwilliams=
.co.nz">Abigail.Collin@wynnwilliams.co.nz</a>&gt;; Richard Hargreaves &lt;<=
a href=3D"mailto:Richard.Hargreaves@wynnwilliams.co.nz">Richard.Hargreaves@=
wynnwilliams.co.nz</a>&gt;; Bryan Strong &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Bryan.Strong=
@tower.co.nz">Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;;
 Kelly Mason &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Kelly.Mason@tower.co.nz">Kelly.Mason@tow=
er.co.nz</a>&gt;; Arna Neems &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Arna.Neems@tower.co.nz">=
Arna.Neems@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;; Lance O'Riley &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Lance.O=
Riley@tower.co.nz">Lance.ORiley@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;<br>
<b>Subject:</b> RE: C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport [WW-ACTIV=
E.FID3167762]</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Raffaella,</s=
pan><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thank you for the e=
mail below.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We can confirm that=
 testing can commence at 2pm on Friday October 17.
</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We will test from s=
ample sites as required to complete a full and thorough determination of an=
y potential contamination, inclusive of all the areas which you have referr=
ed to below.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">You may undertake y=
our own independent testing at any stage; however, Tower would only conside=
r reimbursement for testing which is - a) claim related &amp; b) testing wh=
ich is outside of that which Tower will
 complete. </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I am confident that=
 the Tower Insurance testing will be transparent, quantified by lab results=
, and adequate to provide comfort for all parties.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Clarified scope =
of testing as follows:</span></u><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 =
lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">150mm diameter inspection portals cu=
t in wall cavities of every room on the first floor at a height of 300 mm o=
f floor level and directly underneath
 the top plate.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=
=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0p=
t">Testing of the roof cavity at the soffit junction where potential contam=
inants may have risen through the wall cavity. Testing of the roof cavity at
 the apex where smoke may have accumulated.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=
=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo6"><sp=
an style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Testing of the underside of the rear large up=
per deck.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"mar=
gin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Test=
ing of the basement utilizing all exposed framing cavities and 150mm testin=
g portals cut into any remining ceiling linings in the basemen area.</span>=
<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso=
-list:l0 level1 lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Any additional sampl=
e sites that we feel are required during testing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>=
<o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">To ensure effect=
ual testing it would be beneficial if you could confirm the following:</spa=
n></u><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"4" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 =
lfo3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">That the chlorine was located in the=
 laundry room downstairs at the time of the fire.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li=
 class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo=
3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">The quantity of the chlorine that was i=
n that room at the time of the fire.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"Mso=
ListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3"><span styl=
e=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Where there any
<u>other chemicals</u> that were located in that same room, or anywhere els=
e downstairs. &nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Beyond completing t=
esting and providing laboratory results as described above, I am certain th=
e most productive action we can make towards progressing the claim is to ha=
ve a meeting where we can discuss the
 overall claim response process, providing a forum for you to table any que=
stions, or concerns that you may hold. Those concerns can be responded to, =
and the responses can be documented via minutes with actions and agreements=
 detailed in the minutes providing
 a framework for moving forward with a pre-agreed and productive pathway. I=
 believe this would be very worthwhile and will provide us all with detail,=
 clarity, and documentation that we can all use to our benefit.
</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Your lawyers and ad=
visors would of course be welcome to attend this meeting.</span><o:p></o:p>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I look forward to s=
eeing you again on Friday.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Kind Regards,</span=
><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant. &nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
